# Drizzle ORM Patterns

## Schema Organization

- Define schema in separate files per table: `posts.ts`, `users.ts`, `comments.ts`, `tags.ts`.
- Export schema and relations from each file.
- Re-export from `schema/index.ts`.

```typescript
// schema/posts.ts
import { relations } from 'drizzle-orm';
import { integer, sqliteTable, text } from 'drizzle-orm/sqlite-core';

export const posts = sqliteTable('posts', {
  id: text('id').primaryKey(),
  title: text('title').notNull(),
  slug: text('slug').notNull().unique(),
  publishedAt: integer('published_at', { mode: 'timestamp' }),
  createdAt: integer('created_at', { mode: 'timestamp' })
    .notNull()
    .$defaultFn(() => new Date()),
  updatedAt: integer('updated_at', { mode: 'timestamp' })
    .notNull()
    .$defaultFn(() => new Date()),
});

export const postsRelations = relations(posts, ({ one, many }) => ({
  author: one(users, { fields: [posts.authorId], references: [users.id] }),
  comments: many(comments),
}));
```

## Timestamps

- Use `integer('column', { mode: 'timestamp' })` for date columns.
- Use `$defaultFn(() => new Date())` for auto-generated values.

```typescript
createdAt: integer('created_at', { mode: 'timestamp' })
  .notNull()
  .$defaultFn(() => new Date()),
```

## Mutations

- Always use `.returning()` on insert, update, and delete for typed results.

```typescript
// ✅ Good
const [created] = await db.insert(posts).values(data).returning();
const [updated] = await db.update(posts).set(updates).where(eq(posts.id, id)).returning();
const [deleted] = await db.delete(posts).where(eq(posts.id, id)).returning();

// ❌ Bad - No returning
await db.insert(posts).values(data);
```

## Prepared Statements

- Use `.prepare()` for frequent queries (e.g. by slug, by id) to avoid re-parsing.

```typescript
import { eq, sql } from 'drizzle-orm';

const getPostBySlug = db
  .select()
  .from(posts)
  .where(eq(posts.slug, sql.placeholder('slug')))
  .prepare();
```

## Relations

- Define `relations()` for each table with foreign keys.
- Use `one()` for single relation, `many()` for collections.

```typescript
export const postsRelations = relations(posts, ({ one, many }) => ({
  author: one(users, { fields: [posts.authorId], references: [users.id] }),
  comments: many(comments),
}));
```

## Migrations

- Use `drizzle-kit generate` for schema changes.
- Run migrations with `drizzle-kit migrate` or `drizzle-kit push`.

```bash
pnpm drizzle-kit generate
pnpm drizzle-kit migrate
```
